Contributor Code of Conduct
As contributors and maintainers of this project, we pledge to foster a welcoming and inclusive environment for everyone. We are committed to creating a space where all individuals, regardless of their background or identity, feel respected and valued.

Our Standards
We aim to uphold the following standards to promote a positive environment:

ðŸŸ¢ Expected Behaviors
Be respectful and inclusive of differing viewpoints and experiences.
Show kindness and empathy in all interactions.
Use constructive feedback to foster collaboration and growth.
Respect personal boundaries and maintain professionalism.
ðŸ”´ Unacceptable Behaviors
Harassment, discrimination, or derogatory comments of any kind.
Personal attacks, insults, or threats.
Trolling or other disruptive actions that hinder productive discussions.
Publishing others' private information (such as contact details) without consent.
Scope
This Code of Conduct applies to:

All project spaces, including but not limited to GitHub repositories, discussions, pull requests, and issue trackers.
Public spaces where individuals represent the project or its community.
Reporting Violations
If you experience or witness any unacceptable behavior, please report it by contacting the project maintainers at:
email@example.com

All reports will be reviewed and investigated confidentially. Appropriate actions will be taken to address the issue.

Enforcement
Project maintainers have the right to:

Remove, edit, or reject comments, commits, code, or other contributions that do not align with this Code of Conduct.
Temporarily or permanently ban any contributor for violations.
Acknowledgments
This Code of Conduct is inspired by the Contributor Covenant, version 2.1, and other open-source guidelines.
